her%20head%20and%20used%20holy%20oils%20to%20bestow%20dignity%2C%20sacredness%2C%20strength%2C%20and%20spiritual%20essence%20upon%20her.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThousands%20flocked%20to%20Turangawaewae%2C%20the%20King%20movement's%20meeting%20spot%2C%20to%20bid%20farewell%20to%20him%20in%20a%20traditional%20funeral%20ceremony.%20After%20his%20daughter's%20anointment%2C%20the%20King's%20coffin%20was%20transported%20by%20hearse%20to%20the%20Waikato%20River.%20From%20there%2C%20it%20was%20floated%20in%20a%20flotilla%20of%20traditional%20Maori%20waka%2C%20or%20canoes%2C%20to%20Taupiri%20Mountain%2C%20where%20he%20was%20to%20be%20buried%20with%20other%20royals%20and%20high-profile%20Maori.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Maori%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fall-you-need-to-know-about-sultan-hassanal-bolkiah-and-bruneis-royal-family-6480250%5C%22%3Emonarchy%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewas%20established%20back%20in%201858%20to%20fight%20colonisation%20and%20protect%20M%C4%81ori%20culture%20and%20land%20from%20intruders.%20Although%20the%20monarch%20is%20primarily%20ceremonial%20and%20has%20little%20official%20authority%2C%20it%20is%20nevertheless%20regarded%20by%20many%20tribes%20as%20the%20supreme%20chief.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnWith%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20M%C4%81ori%20cultural%20studies%20from%20Waikato%20University%2C%20Nga%20Wai%20has%20served%20on%20several%20boards%2C%20including%20the%20Te%20Kohanga%20Reo%20National%20Trust%2C%20an%20organisation%20charged%20with%20revitalising%20the%20Maori%20language%2C%20according%20to%201News.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnHer%20anointment%20comes%20amid%20strained%20racial%20relations%20in%20New%20Zealand.%20Since%20assuming%20power%20last%20year%2C%20the%20centre-right%20coalition%20in%20New%20Zealand%20has%20begun%20to%20roll%20back%20the%20policies%20of%20the%20previous%20administration%2C%20especially%20those%20that%20supported%20the%20official%20use%20of%20the%20Maori%20language%2C%20improved%20li