now%20at%20Tata%20Cliq%2C%20for%20breaching%20confidentiality%20and%20poaching%20former%20employees.%20Nykaa%20is%20seeking%20over%20Rs%2020%20crore%20in%20damages%20from%20Asthana%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbeauty-brand-nykaa-sues-former-top-official-for-contract-breach-poaching-124090500111_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbeauty-brand-nykaa-sues-former-top-official-for-contract-breach-poaching-124090500111_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbeauty-brand-nykaa-sues-former-top-official-for-contract-breach-poaching-124090500111_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Made%20By%20Astronauts%20For%20Astronauts%2C%20Boeing%20Starliner%20To%20Return%20Without%20Them%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Boeing%20Starliner%20on%20which%20Indian-origin%20NASA%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20flew%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20on%20June%205%20was%20touted%20as%20a%20space%20capsule%20made%20by%20astronauts%20for%20astronauts%20but%2C%20much%20to%20the%20embarrassment%20of%20Boeing%2C%20is%20now%20set%20to%20return%20without%20any%20human%20spacefarers.%20The%20return%20journey%2C%20in%20autonomous%20mode%2C%20is%20slated%20for%20September%206%20and%20the%20Starliner%20is%20expected%20to%20land%20about%20six%20hours%20after%20it%20undocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Starliner%2C%20whose%20development%20was%20plagued%20by%20delays%2C%20was%20on%20its%20first%20crewed%20test%20flight%2C%20carrying%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20Barry%20%26quot%3BButch%26quot%3B%20Wilmore%20for%20what%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20an%20eight-day%20mission.%20The%20two%20astronauts%20have%20been%20at%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20since%20June%206%20and%20their%20stay%20kept%20getting%20extended%20because%20of%20propulsion%20issues%20on%20the%20Starliner.%20NASA%20announced%20on%20August%2024%20that%20the%20astronauts%20would%20return%20to%20Earth%20in%20February%202025%20and%20the%20Boeing%20spacecraft%20would%20come%20back%20without%20its%20crew.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20uncrewed%20return%20allows%20NASA%20and%20Boeing%20to%20continue%20gathering%20testing%20data%20on%20the%20Starliner%20during%20its%20flight%20home%20while%20also%20allowing%20it%20not%20to%20accept%20more%20risk%20than%20is%20necessary%20for%20its%20crew.%20NASA%20officials%20said%20the%20decision%20was%20%26quot%3Bunanimous%26quot%3B%20on%20its%20part%2C%20while%20Boeing%20asserted%20it%20could%20return%20the%20Starliner%20both%20with%20or%20without%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Tense%20Meeting'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20agency%20has%20confirmed%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20get%20the%20spacecraft%20to%20return%20without%20crew%20was%20taken%20at%20a%20%26quot%3Btense%26quot%3B%20meeting%20between%20NASA%20and%20Boeing%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20decision%2C%20NASA%20chief%20Senator%20Bill%20Nelson%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20former%20astronaut%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSpaceflight%20is%20risky%2C%20even%20at%20its%20safest%20and%20most%20routine.%20A%20test%20flight%2C%20by%20nature%2C%20is%20neither%20safe%20nor%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20keep%20Butch%20and%20Suni%20(Sunita%20Williams)%20aboard%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20and%20bring%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20home%20without%20crew%20is%20the%20result%20of%20our%20commitment%20to%20safety%20-%20our%20core%20value%20and%20our%20North%20Star.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoeing%2C%20on%20its%20part%2C%20said%20it%20remains%20confident%20in%20the%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20return%20safely%20with%20crew.%20%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20support%20NASA's%20requests%20for%20additional%20testing%2C%20data%2C%20analysis%20and%20reviews%20to%20affirm%20the%20spacecraft's%20safe%20undocking%20and%20landing%20capabilities.%20Our%20confidence%20is%20based%20on%20this%20abundance%20of%20valuable%20testing%20from%20Boeing%20and%20NASA.%20The%20testing%20has%20confirmed%20that%2027%20of%2028%20RCS%20(reaction%20control%20system)%20thrusters%20are%20healthy%20and%20back%20to%20full%20operational%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%26quot%3BStarliner's%20propulsion%20system%20also%20maintains%20redundancy%20and%20the%20helium%20levels%20remain%20stable.%20The%20data%20also%20supports%20root%20cause%20assessments%20for%20the%20helium%20and%20thruster%20issues%20and%20flight%20rationale%20for%20Starliner%20and%20its%20crew's%20return%20to%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERequirements%20Unmet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20NASA%2C%20having%20burnt%20its%20fingers%20after%20the%20twin%20accidents%20of%20the%20Challenger%20and%20Columbia%20space%20shuttles%2C%20did%20not%20want%20to%20take%20any%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20NASA%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Buncertainty%20and%20lack%20of%20expert%20concurrence%20does%20not%20meet%20the%20agency's%20safety%20and%20performance%20requirements%20for%20human%20spaceflight%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20said%20the%20space%20capsule%20which%20Indian%20origin%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20had%20piloted%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20is%20the%20most%20modern%20crew%20module%20and%20has%20been%20designed%20to%20ensure%20that%20astronauts%20who%20fly%20in%20it%20are%20safe%20and%20comfortable.%20Ms%20Williams%20herself%20has%20her%20imprint%20on%20almost%20all%20aspects%20of%20the%20spacecraft%20as%20she%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20its%20making%20for%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalypso%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20released%20by%20Boeing%2C%20the%20Starliner%20has%20a%20height%20of%205%20metres%20with%20both%20the%20crew%20module%20and%20service%20module%2C%20a%20diameter%20of%204.6%20metres%2C%20and%20weighs%2013%2C000%20kg%20at%20lift-off.%20The%20Starliner%20is%20designed%20to%20accommodate%20a%20maximum%20crew%20of%20seven%2C%20but%20NASA%20missions%20will%20carry%20a%20crew%20of%20four%20to%20five.%20Each%20crew%20module%20is%20designed%20to%20fly%20up%20to%2010%20missions%2C%20so%20it%20is%20partially%20reusable.%20The%20service%20modules%2C%20however%2C%20are%20made%20for%20each%20mission%20as%20they%20get%20jettisoned%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Crew%20Space%20Transportation%20(CST)-100%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20was%20designed%20for%20a%20mix%20of%20crew%20and%20cargo%20for%20missions%20to%20low-Earth%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Williams%2C%20who%20had%20also%20called%20the%20Starliner%20a%20'fantastic%20spacecraft'%2C%20was%20given%20the%20opportunity%20to%20name%20the%20spacecraft%20she%20would%20fly%20in%20and%20decided%20to%20call%20it%20'Calypso'%20-%20after%20the%20famous%20ship%20on%20which%20the%20French%20oceanographer%20and%20legendary%20filmmaker%20Jacques-Yves%20Cousteau%20explored%20the%20oceans%20when%20she%20was%20still%20a%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20making%20of%20the%20Starliner%20was%20much%20delayed%20and%20went%20way%20over%20the%20budget%2C%20and%20some%20say%20the%20same%20problems%20which%20have%20beset%20the%20Boeing%20Company%20in%20its%20aviation%20business%20may%20be%20plaguing%20the%20space%20side%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20NASA%20had%20awarded%20a%20%24%204.2%20billion%20contract%20to%20Boeing%20for%20making%20the%20Starliner%20from%20scratch%20and%20it%20managed%20to%20go%20on%20its%20first%20human%20spaceflight%20only%20this%20June%20-%20ten%20years%20later.%20In%20comparison%2C%20Space%20X%2C%20which%20was%20given%20a%20similar%20contract%20for%20the%20development%20of%20Crew%20Dragon%2C%C2%A0%20delivered%20it%20at%20an%20estimated%20cost%20of%20%24%202.6%20billion%20and%20has%20been%20ferrying%20astronauts%20since%202020.%20Ms%20Williams%20and%20Mr%20Wilmore%20will%20also%20be%20returning%20to%20Earth%20aboard%20the%20Crew%20Dragon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDevelopment%20To%20Continue%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2024%2C%20the%20NASA%20chief%20said%20he%20had%20100%25%20confidence%20that%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20developed%20but%20asserted%20that%20the%20agency%20had%20awarded%20a%20fixed-price%20contract%20to%20Boeing%2C%20meaning%20that%20the%20company%20will%20have%20to%20bear%20the%20extra%20costs%20for%20its%20full%20certification%20as%20a%20human%20space%20flight-worthy%20vehicle%20at%20its%20own%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Starliner%20had%20also%20been%20making%20headlines%20recently%20for%20%26quot%3Bstrange%20noises%26quot%3B%20emanating%20from%20it%2C%20which%20have%20now%20been%20identified%20as%20feedback%20from%20a%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725507120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fal1jc96g_boeing-starliner_625x300_05_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmade-by-astronauts-for-astronauts-boeing-starliner-to-return-without-them-6494023%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Boeing%20Starliner%20on%20which%20Indian-origin%20NASA%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20flew%20to%20ISS%20on%20June%205%20was%20touted%20as%20a%20space%20capsule%20made%20by%20astronauts%20for%20astronauts%20but%2C%20much%20to%20the%20embarrassment%20of%20Boeing%2C%20is%20now%20set%20to%20return%20without%20any%20humans.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmade-by-astronauts-for-astronauts-boeing-starliner-to-return-without-them-6494023%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Georgia%20school%20shooting%3A